weapons system.

00:14:13.410 --> 00:14:16.200
It's basically a spear chucker.

00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:19.870
And I had never, ever
heard of this weapon.

00:14:19.870 --> 00:14:24.040
And I ended up in an elimination
challenge going head to head,

00:14:24.040 --> 00:14:27.345
and I had one hour with
an atlatl specialist.

00:14:27.345 --> 00:14:28.720
And believe it or
not, yes, there

00:14:28.720 --> 00:14:33.100
are atlatl specialists
who are quite skilled.

00:14:33.100 --> 00:14:37.060
And I had to create a
checklist for myself, because

00:14:37.060 --> 00:14:40.000
for me, that's just the
way that I learn things

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:42.820
right to bring
clarity and structure

00:14:42.820 --> 00:14:45.220
to ambiguous situations.

00:14:45.220 --> 00:14:49.660
And then it's about repeating
the checklist and the steps

00:14:49.660 --> 00:14:53.650
over and over and
over and over again.

00:14:53.650 --> 00:14:55.780
And a quick reference
point, Malcolm Gladwell,

00:14:55.780 --> 00:14:58.300
in one of his books,
famously stated

00:14:58.300 --> 00:15:02.620
it takes 10,000
repetitions in order

00:15:02.620 --> 00:15:07.990
to even begin to be a master
of that particular skill.

00:15:07.990 --> 00:15:12.670
And so I remember having
kind of that 10,000 number

00:15:12.670 --> 00:15:15.190
just ingrained in my
head and thinking,

00:15:15.190 --> 00:15:17.650
OK, with this
atlatl challenge, I

00:15:17.650 --> 00:15:22.120
need to at least get like 1,000
repetitions of my checklist

00:15:22.120 --> 00:15:23.440
in my framework.

00:15:23.440 --> 00:15:27.400
And I only had maybe 12 hours.

00:15:27.400 --> 00:15:31.930
Basically, it was like,
